Description: Minimalist speech-to-text for Linux
 Prosody is a lightweight speech-to-text application that runs in the
 background on Linux systems. It uses OpenAI's Whisper model for accurate
 transcription and features:
 .
  * Global hotkey activation (double-tap Ctrl)
  * Visual waveform indicator during recording
  * Cancel recording with double-tap Escape
  * Automatic text insertion into any application
  * Minimal resource usage when idle
 .
 Note: On first run, Prosody will download the Whisper model (~140MB).
 For full functionality, PyTorch is recommended but will be installed
 automatically if not present.